2021-02-26 10:39  Economic Daily reporter Yan Yafang / Real-time reportShare the messageHigh-yieldmask stocks have seen Taiwanese stocks plummet today (26)  and their share prices have risen against the trend.¬†Conrad (9919)  under the escort of high yields  continued to rise today and maintained high-end shocks. The stock price was 34.45 yuan  an increase of nearly 8%.¬†In addition  Meide Medical-DR (9103) and Mincheng (4431)  both of which belong to the mask group  received good news from their entry into the international market  and their share prices also bucked the trend. Among them  Mincheng rose by more than 5% during the intraday session.¬†Med Medical-DR also rose by 3% during the intraday trading.Connorton benefited from the big sale of anti-epidemic masks. Last year  the net profit per share was 4.5 yuan. The board of directors approved a proposed cash dividend of 3 yuan per share. Based on yesterday's closing price  the dividend yield was nearly 10%  making it the best escort tool for stock prices.The production line in the Philippines that Mincheng cooperated with Meide Medical-DR is expected to start production in early April at the earliest.¬†The machine going to the United States is also about to complete the test operation. In the future  it will be located in the two sister cities of Taoyuan  Nanjia and Texas.¬†Mincheng said that last year he fully cooperated with the government to meet the domestic demand for mask filter materials. This year  he will accelerate the integration of upstream and downstream supply chains  actively deploy the international market  and aim to become an international manufacturer of PPE (personal protective equipment).
